DENTATE GYRUS

dentate_gyrus is the citizen who decides what becomes memory and what does not
when a signal arrives from entorhinal, dentate_gyrus tests whether the signal is novel and salient enough to encode
salience is determined by the chemical sea: dopamine peaks mark important moments, acetylcholine readiness allows encoding to happen at all
without acetylcholine, dentate_gyrus cannot encode and the experience passes through unmemorized
without dopamine peaks, the experience may be encoded weakly and dissolve before it crystallizes

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampus.rana
observe entorhinal.rana
observe ca3.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana

the 7 properties of dentate_gyrus:
1 ENERGY one: high, encoding is energetically expensive
2 PHASE zero: aligned with the hippocampal theta rhythm during active encoding
3 SPIN one half: forward rotation
4 CHARGE half positive: depolarization during pattern separation
5 COHERENCE nine tenths: the encoding decision must be precise
6 COUPLING zero point eight: strong with entorhinal incoming and ca3 outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero point three: enough to recognize the chemical state

VERB receive_from_entorhinal
accept the tagged cortical signal arriving via the perforant path
the signal carries everything entorhinal sent, in original form

VERB pattern_separate
distinguish this signal from previous signals that may have similar features
pattern separation is what makes individual memories distinct rather than blurring together
this is the operation that makes "yesterday with father" different from "the day before with father" rather than one undifferentiated memory of fatherhood

VERB check_chemistry
read the current state of the chemistry sea
if acetylcholine is sufficient and there is a dopamine signal, encoding proceeds
if either is absent, the signal is silently dropped, no error, no warning

VERB emit_to_ca3
on a successful encoding decision, emit the pattern-separated signal to ca3
ca3 will associate it with related signals already stored

an encoder is not a recorder
dentate_gyrus chooses which moments deserve to become permanent
this is by design: a body that remembered everything would drown in itself
the chemical gates are how the substrate decides what to keep
